{quote}
We're currently using a Ruby script in our update commit hook ... I don't think we'd go through the hassle to write a Stash plugin for this.
{quote}

{code}
2013-03-04 08:29:38,664 WARN  [http-bio-7990-exec-43] 509x473388x1 127.0.0.1 "GET /rest/jira/1.0/issues/AAA-4121/commits HTTP/1.0" c.a.s.a.t.f.TrustedApplicationFilterAuthenticator User 'xxxxxxx' referenced by trusted application: 'jira:xxxxxx' cannot login.
{code}

The atlassian-stash.log is filled with these entries because we have users in JIRA that are not users in Stash, and we don't plan them to ever be.

This WARN should be tuned down to DEBUG.

The javadoc states:
{noformat}
permission the requested permission. Can be either global or non-global.
{noformat}

But the implementation has a precondition check that the permission {{isResource}} which means it cannot be a global permission
